-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Milpo, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-07-20T18:44:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/peru-stocks-candente-milpo-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:17 p.m. in Lima.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.4 percent to 20,040.73. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.2 percent to 2,672.55.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, fell 1.8 percent to 54 cents after copper slumped the
most in a month in  New York .  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, slid 1.1 percent to $31.70.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1)  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
and silver producer, dropped 1.3 percent to 3 soles as zinc
declined in  London .  Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1)  (MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and lead producer
controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., fell 1.2
percent to 4 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
